INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (128, 3, '2010-11-08 23:37:53', '2010-11-09 03:37:53', 'On a grey New England weekend in November 2010 fourteen people gathered at the Osher Center (a branch of the Brigham and Womens Hospital) in Chestnut Hill, Boston to begin their training of Manual Trigger-Point Therapy (MTT). They came from as far afield as Nevada, Maryland, Maine and New York. Some had been waiting for nearly a year. (See one of my previous blogs to see how much I admire persistence.)

