INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (202, 2, '2010-12-30 13:35:46', '2010-12-30 18:35:46', '<div class="mceTemp mceIEcenter"><dl id="attachment_203" class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 310px;"> <dt class="wp-caption-dt"><a href="http://www.360nmt.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Screen-shot-2010-12-30-at-11.05.24-AM.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-203" title="what is your 360?" src="http://www.360nmt.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Screen-shot-2010-12-30-at-11.05.24-AM-300x283.png" alt="" width="300" height="283" /></a></dt> </dl></div>
The meaning and interpretation of the <strong>360 NMT logo</strong> continues to evolve. A client recently reminded me of a segment from the T.S. Eliot poem, "Four Quartets," which I think embodies the purpose of receiving NMT:<em>
</em>

<em>We shall not cease from exploration
And the end of all our exploring
Will be to arrive where we started
And know the place for the first time.</em>

The common thread between all of our injury clients at 360 NMT is their desire to heal and to get back to doing what they love, pain free. This mirrors Eliot\'s line about arriving "where we started" -- before an injury.

The "exploration" can be daunting. It requires time, accountability, focus and steadfast dedication. The pain free moments during a healing journey make it all worthwhile. Feeling freedom in the body is exhilarating.

As this year comes to a close, what is your personal 360 for 2011? What do you want to get out and do with your body?

I make the same New Year\'s resolution every year: I want to dance again. Being a former professional dancer, the anticipation of pain coupled with strong self criticism beats me to the dance studio every time. My excuses: "I have a foot injury, I\'ve gained some weight, I\'ve lost flexibility, I don\'t have enough time, I\'m almost 40!!"

Frequently, I speak with my clients about the psychosocial component of injury and subsequent kinesiophobia that can develop. Over this holiday week, I have taken a hard look in the mirror. I am not practicing what I preach nor embodying my company\'s mission. I\'ve ceased my own exploration before even beginning it.

My 360 for 2011 is to feel the marley under my feet again. I want to engage with the Boston dance community and rekindle the joy dancing brings to my heart and spirit. I might not leap as high as when I was 22, but I\'m going to try. To start, I have to unwind 16 years of doing massage with less-than-perfect body mechanics. In the upcoming blog entries, I intend to document my neuromuscular re-education by signing up for treatment and training with our <a href="http://www.360nmt.com/colleagues.php">360 NMT colleagues</a>. I hope it will inspire some learning (and laughter)!

I believe that we can all "know a place for the first time."

Happy New Year,

<em>Katie</em>', 'My 360 for 2011', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'my-360-for-2011', '', '', '2010-12-30 13:45:41', '2010-12-30 18:45:41', '', 0, 'http://www.360nmt.com/blog/?p=202', 0, 'post', '', 0) ; 
