INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (207, 2, '2010-12-30 12:39:11', '2010-12-30 17:39:11', '[caption id="attachment_203" align="aligncenter" width="300" caption="what is your 360?"]<a href="http://www.360nmt.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Screen-shot-2010-12-30-at-11.05.24-AM.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-203" title="what is your 360?" src="http://www.360nmt.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Screen-shot-2010-12-30-at-11.05.24-AM-300x283.png" alt="" width="300" height="283" /></a>[/caption]

The meaning and interpretation of the <strong>360 NMT logo</strong> continues to evolve. A client recently reminded me of a segment from the T.S. Eliot poem, "Four Quartets," which I think embodies the purpose of receiving NMT:<em>
</em>

<em>We shall not cease from exploration
And the end of all our exploring
Will be to arrive where we started
And know the place for the first time.</em>

The common thread between all of our injury clients at 360 NMT is the desire to heal and to get back to doing what they love, pain free. This mirrors Elliot\'s line about arriving "where we started" -- before an injury.

The "exploration" can be daunting and painful. It requires accountability and steadfast dedication. However, moments of movement without pain and regaining freedom in the body are exhilarating.

What is your 360 for 2011? What do you want to get out and do with your body?

As a former dancer, I make the same New Year\'s resolution every year: I want to dance again. the anticipation of pain and strong self criticism beats me before I make it to the dance studio. Excuses: "I have a foot injury, I\'ve gained some weight, I\'ve lost flexibility, I\'m almost 40!!"

Frequently, I speak with the 360 NMT staff about the psychosocial component of injury and subsequent kinesiophobia that can develop. But if I take a hard look in the mirror, I am not practicing what I preach. I\'ve ceased my exploration before even beginning.

My 360 for 2011 is to find the freedom in my body, mind (and schedule!) to dance again. I might not leap as high as when I was 19, but I will explore the path back to dancing. To start, I must unwind 16 years of doing bodywork with faulty biomechanics (aka, pushing muscles all day long over a hypermobile pelvis and weak gluteals).', 'My 360 for 2011', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '202-revision-3', '', '', '2010-12-30 12:39:11', '2010-12-30 17:39:11', '', 202, 'http://www.360nmt.com/blog/?p=207', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
